plurry
Homonym Number:
Word Class:adverb
Sense Number:
Definition:`stage-Maori' representation of <i>bloody</i>, occasionally used as a general euphemision (from Maori transposition of English /B/ as /P/ and /D/ as /R/)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also used as an adj. a plurry mess
Citations
Date: 4/8/1900
Source: New Zealand Free Lance
Author:
Vol / Page: 10
Edition:
Quote: A Greytown Maori describing the Lydite shell and its effects to a brother Maori, said: "By cripes! he the plurry boy to kill the Poa. When he burst, as soon you hear the smell, you dead!"
