Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 85
Edition:
Quote: <i>plurry</i> bloody; pidgin in Australia and New Zealand; Partridge says it is from Aboriginal's natural use of the word, OEDS says NZA slang, Turner thinks it a convention of journalists rather than Maori, in support of which was the slanguage of the character Hori in the bestselling book <i>The Half-Gallon Jar. </i>
Notes:

